{"type":"message","id":"4cc918bf","parentId":"7021670c","timestamp":"2026-04-24T00:01:05.943Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Considering volume analysis**\n\nI'm thinking about how to compute a volume breakout compared to averages, and possibly using a simple RSI indicator. I wonder if a Python script might be the best approach for this, maybe incorporating a straightforward MACD/RSI calculation. It seems like a useful way to analyze the data effectively! I'd like to explore these tools further to gain better insights into the overall performance. This feels like it could be a productive strategy for data analysis.","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_0059dd7f9d4e6a410169eab2ae8fd4819a8c89ef7300487a13\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp6rKxl4sV1OUFOemXp5DGzlqsuiTWhAgb2Bn_EBYGkD16K2P1XwTpUgIEZYSSGqOdCR6X-ESFASf-L-Eqx0LCLT3O51EcCQb1n8tWEe1SuLmUHiRaKhWqxzuPTGoLaY7SN086OeMJDJG4uHLCXxaQ8rqsbh-k-guBlcj-dqLhFpm6OTX9haUFe4KoE3KfuJowAMVi_DyGuYjsFyVwA390lsYHtI-mQ-A3dpzcbKw7OGX3iaNwNrsIraV18u1DT-4-qQlC9CD0hGrtK6bRQzWonP8xhbjnlwmetI36DziFN0AYbV7HacljjXVKCLkI_1GfvXnfpY2jcLpkJQp76xW4-_j_szS_Usw_hvsl-C-PbOIsVUIGfrmkepzIRPJJAj-8nTc370lvEwh5qTaphbS4PpDX2U5LBOAQAbiiRQV0fATv6jekI1_RgiqEFXxmja_nSKLudVFGV9Swn97XRBWi4QTpOM27WiYTgbH1f0ocf_H0hIxw6N0smYfaG3mvvgfcfxx-yS2j_BsplOrDsHMRy_GVM260rXYNZVbhrx34d6NXAXOEUj0l-aX0Bb5AQX0Q-ZPbVfba4Ad0RI0WfAWCOyZP2npt7AHYeH_po4WDhY4vXlLjteujgXQhwYeOx-bnln0yXZ7OF6s9m575aQNYLD4TiMlEuJv-zg0L-mZNQDxbaLpoXMIeOM-sa1ZuT-9N61e_sKu_LXLpFTSdDczl6ay99aH-toWMujWur0NakonSMu4xEMlarcCCjGgLNsvdBmrJ3JnXPOEmW2GN3WwPSU2UcnpCYrlBLuGM0q0bnVV8DioHketUartPk9fsDswuSfHEGzIELHIG2JGgpsCczLiFSjpUwLzhrkQbkpDxGfoCUWDLK1y6v0MAP3fezzQq5f2HhcQ8rDYCnNqDGl_D4eFmgy1yeoyg3HfkrDmfVb_tqyG-JS05ZRqfSTCzRcZKEFojAunYg6WHavG_Zn2F6mZFtmMbAIzQ60_i0uDi6ys42NrFn2vo_lYWkxrfDPzi2bfJTIt7i3zcbixLjtzFfd1ymBINsZBGzEG_usc-2IxiJ10=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering volume analysis**\\n\\nI'm thinking about how to compute a volume breakout compared to averages, and possibly using a simple RSI indicator. I wonder if a Python script might be the best approach for this, maybe incorporating a straightforward MACD/RSI calculation. It seems like a useful way to analyze the data effectively! I'd like to explore these tools further to gain better insights into the overall performance. This feels like it could be a productive strategy for data analysis.\"}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_OnZeoZigByrhlZJOs2Q6lN4g|fc_0059dd7f9d4e6a410169eab2b13960819aa9b4dbe8afbd28de","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 - <<'PY'\nimport akshare as ak\nimport pandas as pd\nfrom datetime import datetime, timedelta\nimport json\nsymbol='600487'\nend=datetime.now().strftime('%Y%m%d')\nstart=(datetime.now()-timedelta(days=500)).strftime('%Y%m%d')\nh=ak.stock_zh_a_hist(symbol=symbol, period='daily', start_date=start, end_date=end, adjust='qfq').copy()\nclose=h['收盘'].astype(float)\nvol=h['成交量'].astype(float)\n# RSI14\nchg=close.diff()\ngain=chg.clip(lower=0)\nloss=-chg.clip(upper=0)\nrs=gain.rolling(14).mean()/loss.rolling(14).mean()\nrsi=100-(100/(1+rs))\n# MACD\nema12=close.ewm(span=12, adjust=False).mean()\nema26=close.ewm(span=26, adjust=False).mean()\ndif=ema12-ema26\ndea=dif.ewm(span=9, adjust=False).mean()\nmacd=(dif-dea)*2\n# volume ratio to 5/10/20 avg\nres={\n 'date': str(h.iloc[-1]['日期']),\n 'rsi14': round(float(rsi.iloc[-1]),2),\n 'dif': round(float(dif.iloc[-1]),2),\n 'dea': round(float(dea.iloc[-1]),2),\n 'macd': round(float(macd.iloc[-1]),2),\n 'vol_vs_5': round(float(vol.iloc[-1]/vol.tail(5).mean()),2),\n 'vol_vs_10': round(float(vol.iloc[-1]/vol.tail(10).mean()),2),\n 'vol_vs_20': round(float(vol.iloc[-1]/vol.tail(20).mean()),2),\n}\nprint(json.dumps(res, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2))\nPY","workdir":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/coding-agent","timeout":60},"partialJson":"{\"command\":\"python3 - <<'PY'\\nimport akshare as ak\\nimport pandas as pd\\nfrom datetime import datetime, timedelta\\nimport json\\nsymbol='600487'\\nend=datetime.now().strftime('%Y%m%d')\\nstart=(datetime.now()-timedelta(days=500)).strftime('%Y%m%d')\\nh=ak.stock_zh_a_hist(symbol=symbol, period='daily', start_date=start, end_date=end, adjust='qfq').copy()\\nclose=h['收盘'].astype(float)\\nvol=h['成交量'].astype(float)\\n# RSI14\\nchg=close.diff()\\ngain=chg.clip(lower=0)\\nloss=-chg.clip(upper=0)\\nrs=gain.rolling(14).mean()/loss.rolling(14).mean()\\nrsi=100-(100/(1+rs))\\n# MACD\\nema12=close.ewm(span=12, adjust=False).mean()\\nema26=close.ewm(span=26, adjust=False).mean()\\ndif=ema12-ema26\\ndea=dif.ewm(span=9, adjust=False).mean()\\nmacd=(dif-dea)*2\\n# volume ratio to 5/10/20 avg\\nres={\\n 'date': str(h.iloc[-1]['日期']),\\n 'rsi14': round(float(rsi.iloc[-1]),2),\\n 'dif': round(float(dif.iloc[-1]),2),\\n 'dea': round(float(dea.iloc[-1]),2),\\n 'macd': round(float(macd.iloc[-1]),2),\\n 'vol_vs_5': round(float(vol.iloc[-1]/vol.tail(5).mean()),2),\\n 'vol_vs_10': round(float(vol.iloc[-1]/vol.tail(10).mean()),2),\\n 'vol_vs_20': round(float(vol.iloc[-1]/vol.tail(20).mean()),2),\\n}\\nprint(json.dumps(res, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2))\\nPY\",\"workdir\":\"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/coding-agent\",\"timeout\":60}"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"beecode","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":45237,"output":499,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":45736,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776988843899,"responseId":"resp_0059dd7f9d4e6a410169eab2ad5b10819abe33d0d8200c9fb5"}}
